perl-OpenGL
-------------------------------------------
Perl module to display 3D data using OpenGL, GLU, and GLUT.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-61
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libGL1-7.4.4-1
  libGLU1-7.4.4-1
  libglut3-2.4.0-1
  libX11_6-1.2.2-1
  perl-5.10.0-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  make-3.81-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://search.cpan.org/dist/OpenGL/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/C/CH/CHM/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-OpenGL-0.58-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-OpenGL-0.58-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-OpenGL-0.58-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-OpenGL-0.58-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.58-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 0.57-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin 1.7.


